cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CY

This paper deals with the problem of protecting sensitive user-generated data while still being able to learn predictive models from it. This falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of boosting and random linear classifiers for this purpose, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of cloud services for storage and computation, which falls under the category of databases (cs.DB) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
